OL,3,CCervical smear scandal: Review ordered
OL,4,Cafter reviews - and no public inquiry
OL,6,FHe added: "I acknowledge that this has
OL,7,Fbeen a difficult and challenging time
OL,8,Ffor many people, particularly for the
OL,9,Fwomen who were part of the review and
OL,10,Fthose impacted by cervical cancer, but
OL,11,FI remain committed to understanding
OL,12,Fthe circumstances and events which led
OL,13,Fto the precautionary review of
OL,14,Fcervical cytology in the Southern
OL,15,FTrust."
OL,17,FCampaign group Ladies with Letters
OL,18,Fhave questioned why the minister had
OL,19,F"chosen to ignore the calls from the
OL,20,Fmany women and their families to
OL,21,Festablish a statutory public inquiry".
